__DESCRIPTION__

Over the last couple of years I have been spending almost all of my working time actually coding Perl. This made it worthwhile to optimise my development environment. I'll talk a little about some of the tools I use which allow me to focus more on the actual development problems and less on mechanisms used to create the code.

* Environment: table, chair
* Dual 24" screen
* Keyboard with programmable keys - Logitec G15
* Decent mouse
* Decent Speaker or headphone
* Hardware!  Quiet (SSD ?)
* Operating Systems: Virtual Machines help a lot
* OS: Whatever needed
* Window manager
* Terminal multiplexers: [tmux](http://tmux.sourceforge.net/), [powerline](https://github.com/Lokaltog/powerline) 
* Shell: [zsh](http://www.zsh.org/) 
* Font: Monospace: [Inconsolata](http://levien.com/type/myfonts/inconsolata.html)
* Colour Scheme: [Solarized dark](http://ethanschoonover.com/solarized)  f.lux
* Source Code Control: Git (aliases!)
* Editor: Vim, Emacs
* Vim Plugins:
  * [Pathogene](https://github.com/tpope/vim-pathogen)
  * [YouCompleteMe](https://github.com/Valloric/YouCompleteMe)
  * [Fugitive](https://github.com/tpope/vim-fugitive)
  * [GitGutter](https://github.com/jisaacks/GitGutter)
  * [signature](https://github.com/kshenoy/vim-signature)
  * [tagbar](http://majutsushi.github.io/tagbar/)
  * [NERD_commenter](http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=1218)
  * [NERD_tree](http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=1658)
  * [snipMate](http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=2540)
  * [surround](http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=1697)
  * [devel-cover](https://metacpan.org/pod/Devel::Cover::Report::Vim)
* ssh
* [mosh](http://mosh.mit.edu/)
* [Putty](http://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/) (for Windows)
* Email: [mutt](http://www.mutt.org/)
* IRC: [irssi](http://www.irssi.org/)

